(68, 1, '2016-10-31 12:12:32', '2016-10-31 09:12:32', '<p class="normal" align="center"><b>General information</b></p>\n<p class="normal" align="center"><b>Eurasian Higher Education Leaders Forum 2016: Higher Education and Modernization of the Economy: Innovative and Entrepreneurial Universities</b></p>\n<p class="normal">The fifth annual Eurasian Higher Education Leaders’ Forum will take place on May 26, 2016 at Nazarbayev University.</p>\n<p class="normal">The Forum aims to bring together education stakeholders to share their ideas and engage in lively debates on issues that higher education leaders are facing worldwide.</p>\n<p class="normal">This year, we have come up with a series of interesting sessions geared to the theme of “<i>Higher Education and Modernization of the Economy: Innovative and Entrepreneurial Universities”. </i></p>\n<p class="normal"><b>Plenary Session</b></p>\n<p class="normal">The session is co-organized with L.N.Gumilyov Eurasian National University in the framework of Astana Economic Forum. Under the umbrella theme, we are arranging an interactive plenary session with following topics:</p>\n<p class="normalCxSpMiddle">●      Entrepreneurial and innovative universities</p>\n<p class="normalCxSpMiddle">●      Role of higher education in the modernization of the economy</p>\n<p class="normalCxSpMiddle">●      The university of the future</p>\n<p class="normalCxSpMiddle">●      Graduate employment and the needs of the economy</p>\n<p class="normal">Leading international and global experts in the fields of education, economics and industry will be participating in the conference.</p>\n<p class="normal"></p>\n<p class="normal">In addition to the plenary session of the Forum, visitors can take part in seminars at which Nazarbayev University will share its experience.</p>\n<p class="normal"></p>\n<p class="normal"><b>Sharing NU Experience</b></p>\n<p class="normal">Sharing Nazarbayev University experience sessions will take place on May 25-26, 2016 and will comprise of seminars on various topics, such as quality enhancement through annual program review; practical details of selection and admission of students to the Nazarbayev University; NU Graduate School of Education’s seminars on curriculum development, teaching and assessment, implementing corporate governance and conducting research in humanities, and many more.</p>\n<p class="normal"></p>\n<p class="normal"><b>Conference proceedings</b></p>\n<p class="normal">Forum participants can submit their articles for publication in the Conference Proceedings indexed in the Thompson Reuters. The guide for authors is available at this<u> link</u>. Conference Proceedings from previous years can be found <u>here.</u></p>\n<p class="normal"><a name="h.q1z8r5wvdzva"></a></p>\n<p class="normal"><a name="h.30j0zll"></a>Participation in the Forum is free of charge.</p>\n<p class="normal"></p>\n<p class="normal">Sincerely,</p>\n<p class="normal">Steering Committee</p>\n<p class="normal">Eurasian Higher Education Leaders Forum</p>', 'Привет, мир!', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '1-autosave-v1', '', '', '2016-10-31 12:12:32', '2016-10-31 09:12:32', '', 1, 'http://ehelf.loc/2016/10/31/1-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
