(88, 1, '2016-11-17 07:37:48', '2016-11-17 04:37:48', 'Dear…..\r\n\r\nWe are honored to invite you and your colleagues to the fifth annual Eurasian Higher Education Leaders’ Forum, an important educational event in the region, which will be held on May 25-26, 2016 at Nazarbayev University. This year the theme of the Forum is <em>"Higher education and modernization of the economy: innovative and entrepreneurial universities"</em>\r\n\r\nWe anticipate lively debates of professionals during the Forum to generate a motivating environment for collaboration and networking between stakeholders of higher education, including students, faculty members, employees, university leaders, policy makers and leaders of public and private sectors.\r\n\r\nThe Forum includes a plenary session with the participation of international experts and series of seminars on sharing best practices used at Nazarbayev University.\r\n\r\n<strong>Plenary session</strong>\r\n\r\nThe main event of the Forum will be held on May 26, 2016 from 9 AM to 11 AM. The event aims to bring together distinguished experts in education from the Eurasian continent and beyond to share their ideas and experience.\r\n\r\nThe panelists of the session will address the following issues: the role of higher education in the modernization of the economy, entrepreneurial and innovative universities, the future of universities, graduate employment and the needs of the economy.\r\n\r\nLeading international and global experts in the fields of education, economics and industry will be participating in the conference.\r\n\r\nParticipants may submit their articles for publication in the Annual Proceedings. The guide for authors and style conventions can be found in the addendum to this letter.\r\n\r\n<strong>Sharing Nazarbayev University experience</strong>\r\n\r\nSharing Nazarbayev University experience sessions will take place on May 25-26, 2016 and will comprise of seminars on various topics, such as quality enhancement through annual program review; practical details of selection and admission of students to the Nazarbayev University; NU Graduate School of Education’s seminars on curriculum development, teaching and assessment, implementing corporate governance and conducting research in humanities, and many more.\r\n\r\nAdditional information regarding the session on sharing NU experience and the guide for authors are enclosed with the present letter. Registration for the Forum sessions and all the detailed information is available on the EHELF official website – <u>www.ehelf.nu.edu.kz</u>. Participation in the Forum is free of charge.\r\n\r\nSincerely,\r\n\r\nSteering Committee\r\n\r\nEurasian Higher Education Leaders Forum', 'About EHELF', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '86-autosave-v1', '', '', '2016-11-17 07:37:48', '2016-11-17 04:37:48', '', 86, 'http://ehelf.loc/2016/11/01/86-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
