(423, 1, '2016-11-14 19:20:32', '2016-11-14 16:20:32', '<strong>Eurasian Higher Education Leaders’ Forum – 2015\r\n\r\nGraduate Employability in the 21st Century\r\n\r\nOverview session</strong>\r\n\r\nOpenning speech: Aslan Sarinzhipov, Minister of Education and Science of the Republic of Kazakhstan\r\n\r\nModerator: Rakhman Alshanov, President of the Association of Higher Educational Institutions of the Republic of Kazakhstan, Rector, "Turan" University, Kazakhstan\r\n\r\nKeynote speaker: Hugh Lauder, Professor of Education and Political Economy, University of Bath, UK\r\n\r\nPanelists:\r\n\r\n-	Berik Kamaliyev, Vice-President,  JSC, National Company “Kazakhstan Temir Zholy” (“Kazakhstan Railways”), Kazakhstan\r\n\r\n-	Erezhep Mambetkaziyev, President, Kazakh-American Free University, Kazakhstan  \r\n\r\n-	Timothy Miller, General Director, Tengizchevroil, Kazakhstan\r\n<hr>\r\n1. Panel session: Global Skills\r\n\r\nModerator: Simon Jones, Provost, Nazarbayev University, Kazakhstan\r\n\r\nKeynote speaker: Jamil Salmi, A Global Tertiary Education Expert, Morocco\r\n\r\nPanelists:\r\n\r\n-	Seeram Ramakrishna, Director, Center for Nanofibers & Nanotechnology, National University of Singapore, Singapore\r\n\r\n-	Jamilya Nurmanbetova, First Vice-Rector, Gumilyov Eurasian National University, Kazakhstan\r\n\r\n-	Duncan van Bergen,Vice President and Country Chair, Shell, Kazakhstan\r\n<hr>\r\n2. Panel session: Perceptions of Employability, Skills and Individual Aspiration in a Diversifying Economy\r\n\r\nModerator: Alan Ruby, Senior Research Fellow, University of Pennsylvania Graduate School of Education, USA\r\n\r\nKeynote speaker: Alper Akdeniz, Managing Partner for Eurasia, PricewaterhouseCoopers (PwC), Kazakhstan\r\n\r\nPanelists:\r\n\r\n-	Arstan Gazaliyev, Rector, Karaganda State Technical University, Kazakhstan\r\n\r\n-	Kanysh Tuleushin, Member of Managing Board, Managing Director, Baiterek National Holding, Kazakhstan\r\n\r\n-	Stavros Yiannouka, Chief Executive Officer, World Innovation Summit for Education (WISE), Qatar\r\n\r\n-	Aida Sagintayeva, Chief Executive Director, Nazarbayev University Graduate School of Education, Kazakhstan\r\n<hr>\r\n3. Panel session: University-Employer-Community Relationships\r\n\r\nModerator: Loretta O''Donnell, Vice-Provost for Academic Affairs, Nazarbayev University, Kazakhstan\r\n\r\nKeynote speaker: Shamsh Kassim-Lakha, Executive Chairman of the Board Executive Committee, University of Central Asia (UCA), Kyrgyzstan\r\n\r\nPanelists:\r\n\r\n-	Matthew Hartley, Professor, Higher Education Division, University of Pennsylvania Graduate School of Education, USA\r\n\r\n-	Abdrakhman Naizabekov, Rector, Rudny Industrial Institute, Kazakhstan\r\n\r\n-	Ivan Klimenko, President, LLP "Stopharm", Kazakhstan\r\n<hr>\r\n4. Panel session: Role of TVET in Education\r\n\r\nModerator: Sabyrzhan Madeyev, Director, Department for Modernization of Vocational and Post-secondary Education of the Ministry of Education and Science of the Republic of Kazakhstan\r\n\r\nKeynote speaker: Geoff Hayward, Head of Education Faculty, University of Cambridge, UK\r\n\r\nPanelists:\r\n\r\n-	Kadyrbek Boribekov, Deputy Chairman, “Kassipkor” National Holding, Kazakhstan\r\n\r\n-	Rainer Goertz, Senior Expert TVET, GIZ Kazakhstan\r\n\r\n-	Marlen Mirzabekov, Chairman of the Management Board, LLP "Kazzinc Holdings", Kazakhstan\r\n\r\n-	Shokan Orazalin, Director, “Higher Technical School of Shchuchinsk” State Municipal, Kazakhstan\r\n<hr>\r\n5. Panel session: Student Transitions and Careers Guidance\r\n\r\nModerator: Kadisha Dairova, Vice-President for Student Affairs and International Cooperation, Nazarbayev University, Kazakshtan\r\n\r\nKeynote speaker: Dina Askarova, Student, School of Humanities and Social Sciences, Nazarbayev University, Kazakhstan\r\n\r\nPanelists:\r\n\r\n-	David Bridges, Professor, University of Cambridge, UK\r\n\r\n-	Sultan Imanzhan, Student, College of Transport and Communication, Kazakhstan\r\n\r\n-	Assel Muk