(623, 1, '2016-11-16 07:39:55', '2016-11-16 04:39:55', 'Registration of Foreign Citizens\r\n\r\nWhen entering Kazakhstan, a foreign citizen gets migration card with entry marks from Boarder Control Department.\r\nUpon arrival in Kazakhstan, the foreign citizen should register with the Local Migration Police Department within 5 days.\r\nPassports of citizens of 28 developed and politically stable countries are registered automatically:\r\n§  together with business, tourist, private, diplomatic and service visas in consular offices of Kazakhstan abroad;\r\n§  or immediately on the state boarder in Boarder Control Departments.\r\nIn above mentioned cases, the foreign citizen does not need register with Migration Police.\r\nPassports of foreign citizens are registered free of charge and executed for up to 3 months.\r\nIn case of delay and/or avoidance of registration, an administrative responsibility is provided in terms of fine and/or exclusion from Kazakhstan with prohibition to enter Kazakhstan for 5 years after such exclusion.\r\n \r\nList of countries:\r\n\r\nAustralia\r\nAustria\r\nBelgium\r\nGermany\r\nGreece\r\nDenmark\r\nIreland\r\nIceland\r\nSoain\r\nItalia\r\nZealand\r\nCanada\r\nLiechtenstein\r\nLuxembourg\r\nMalaysia\r\nMonaco\r\nNetherlands\r\nNorway\r\nPortugal\r\nSingapore\r\nUnited Kingdom of Great Britain and Northern Ireland\r\nUSA\r\nFinland\r\nFrance\r\nSwitzerland\r\nSweden\r\nSouth Korea\r\nJapan\r\n<a href="http://ehelf.loc/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/visa-doc-eng.pdf"><strong>Visa obtaining</strong></a>', 'Kazakhstan Visa Requirements', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '104-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-11-16 07:39:55', '2016-11-16 04:39:55', '', 104, 'http://ehelf.loc/2016/11/16/104-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(624, 1, '2016-11-16 07:41:25', '2016-11-16 04:41:25', '<strong>Registration of Foreign Citizens</strong>\r\n\r\nWhen entering Kazakhstan, a foreign citizen gets migration card with entry marks from Boarder Control Department.\r\nUpon arrival in Kazakhstan, the foreign citizen should register with the Local Migration Police Department within 5 days.\r\nPassports of citizens of 28 developed and politically stable countries are registered automatically:\r\n§  together with business, tourist, private, diplomatic and service visas in consular offices of Kazakhstan abroad;\r\n§  or immediately on the state boarder in Boarder Control Departments.\r\nIn above mentioned cases, the foreign citizen does not need register with Migration Police.\r\nPassports of foreign citizens are registered free of charge and executed for up to 3 months.\r\nIn case of delay and/or avoidance of registration, an administrative responsibility is provided in terms of fine and/or exclusion from Kazakhstan with prohibition to enter Kazakhstan for 5 years after such exclusion.\r\n \r\n<strong>List of countries:</strong>\r\n\r\nAustralia\r\nAustria\r\nBelgium\r\nGermany\r\nGreece\r\nDenmark\r\nIreland\r\nIceland\r\nSoain\r\nItalia\r\nZealand\r\nCanada\r\nLiechtenstein\r\nLuxembourg\r\nMalaysia\r\nMonaco\r\nNetherlands\r\nNorway\r\nPortugal\r\nSingapore\r\nUnited Kingdom of Great Britain and Northern Ireland\r\nUSA\r\nFinland\r\nFrance\r\nSwitzerland\r\nSweden\r\nSouth Korea\r\nJapan\r\n<a href="http://ehelf.loc/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/visa-doc-eng.pdf"><strong>Visa obtaining</strong></a>', 'Kazakhstan Visa Requirements', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '104-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-11-16 07:41:25', '2016-11-16 04:41:25', '', 104, 'http://ehelf.loc/2016/11/16/104-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(625, 1, '2016-11-16 07:43:22', '2016-11-16 04:43:22', '<strong>“Library Connect - 2016:\r\n\r\nEmerging Global Trends in University Library Development”</strong>\r\n\r\nNazarbayev University Library, L.N. Gumilyov Eurasian National University Scientific Library and Academic Library Association of Kazakhstan in part with the Eurasian Higher Education Leaders Forum - 2016 hold:\r\n·       Professional seminar  “Library Connect - 2016: Emerging Global Trends in University Library Development”\r\n·      V international conference “Modern Trends in University Library Development: state, issues, and perspectives-2016”\r\nfor senior specialists and managers of university libraries in Kazakhstan.\r\n\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> May 25-26, 2016\r\n<strong>Venue: </strong>Nazarbayev University and L.N. Gumilyov Eurasian National University\r\n \r\n\r\nThe measures will include lectures, workshops, and presentations by foreign and Kazakhstani academic librarians, as well as consultations and discussions regarding current issues in library and information services for educational and research activities at universities.\r\n \r\nParticipation in the seminar is free of charge.\r\n \r\nTravel, accommodation and meals costs are at the expenses of the participants or sending organizations. \r\n\r\n<strong>Registration</strong> of participants is opened: with presentation by April 30, 2016 (with a presentation) or May 17, 2016 (without a presentation):\r\n·      on the Eurasian Higher Education Leaders Forum website -  https://form.jotform.me/61032813893455\r\n     ·      on the  L.N. Gumilyov Eurasian National University Scientific library website -  http://lib.enu.kz/kz/\r\n\r\n"Library Connect – 2016" seminar will be available online. Please follow this link to register for seminar''s Live Stream.\r\n\r\nThe program you can see  <a href="http://ehelf.loc/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Forum_seminar_program_2016_eng.pdf"> <strong>here </strong></a>\r\n\r\nThe text of a paper for the conference proceedings should be sent to library@enu.kz no later than April 30, 2016.\r\n<strong>\r\nProceedings paper requirements:</strong>\r\nTitle, full author/coauthor name, institution, city, country.\r\nAbstract in 500 characters (including spaces). \r\nThe paper is accepted in electronic format only (Word for Windows; 14 font size, 1.5 line spacing).\r\nThe Organizing Committee reserves the right to include the papers into the program or the proceedings.\r\n<strong>\r\nContact information: </strong>\r\nAnar Dautova: adautova@nu.edu.kz (+7 7172-70-62-73+7 7172-70-62-73, 8-775-786-79-41) \r\nDarya Zvonareva: darya.zvonareva@nu.edu.kz (+7 7172-70-59-41+7 7172-70-59-41, 8-747-256-08-98)\r\n \r\n<strong>\r\nAbout participation and proceedings paper publication:</strong>\r\nGulshat Daribayeva:  library@enu.kz (+ 7 (7172) 70-95-00+ 7 (7172) 70-95-00, 8 -777 331 36 628 -777 331 36 62)', 'Seminar for librarians', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '126-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-11-16 07:43:22', '2016-11-16 04:43:22', '', 126, 'http://ehelf.loc/2016/11/16/126-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
