(637, 1, '2016-11-16 08:52:11', '2016-11-16 05:52:11', '<strong>Eurasian Higher Education Leaders’ Forum – 2015\r\n\r\nGraduate Employability in the 21st Century\r\n\r\nOverview session</strong>\r\n\r\nOpenning speech: Aslan Sarinzhipov, Minister of Education and Science of the Republic of Kazakhstan\r\n\r\nModerator: Rakhman Alshanov, President of the Association of Higher Educational Institutions of the Republic of Kazakhstan, Rector, "Turan" University, Kazakhstan\r\n\r\nKeynote speaker: Hugh Lauder, Professor of Education and Political Economy, University of Bath, UK\r\n\r\nPanelists:\r\n\r\n-	Berik Kamaliyev, Vice-President,  JSC, National Company “Kazakhstan Temir Zholy” (“Kazakhstan Railways”), Kazakhstan\r\n\r\n-	Erezhep Mambetkaziyev, President, Kazakh-American Free University, Kazakhstan  \r\n\r\n-	Timothy Miller, General Director, Tengizchevroil, Kazakhstan\r\n<hr>\r\n1. Panel session: Global Skills\r\n\r\nModerator: Simon Jones, Provost, Nazarbayev University, Kazakhstan\r\n\r\nKeynote speaker: Jamil Salmi, A Global Tertiary Education Expert, Morocco\r\n\r\nPanelists:\r\n\r\n-	Seeram Ramakrishna, Director, Center for Nanofibers & Nanotechnology, National University of Singapore, Singapore\r\n\r\n-	Jamilya Nurmanbetova, First Vice-Rector, Gumilyov Eurasian National University, Kazakhstan\r\n\r\n-	Duncan van Bergen,Vice President and Country Chair, Shell, Kazakhstan\r\n<hr>\r\n2. Panel session: Perceptions of Employability, Skills and Individual Aspiration in a Diversifying Economy\r\n\r\nModerator: Alan Ruby, Senior Research Fellow, University of Pennsylvania Graduate School of Education, USA\r\n\r\nKeynote speaker: Alper Akdeniz, Managing Partner for Eurasia, PricewaterhouseCoopers (PwC), Kazakhstan\r\n\r\nPanelists:\r\n\r\n-	Arstan Gazaliyev, Rector, Karaganda State Technical University, Kazakhstan\r\n\r\n-	Kanysh Tuleushin, Member of Managing Board, Managing Director, Baiterek National Holding, Kazakhstan\r\n\r\n-	Stavros Yiannouka, Chief Executive Officer, World Innovation Summit for Education (WISE), Qatar\r\n\r\n-	Aida Sagintayeva, Chief Executive Director, Nazarbayev University Graduate School of Education, Kazakhstan\r\n<hr>\r\n3. Panel session: University-Employer-Community Relationships\r\n\r\nModerator: Loretta O''Donnell, Vice-Provost for Academic Affairs, Nazarbayev University, Kazakhstan\r\n\r\nKeynote speaker: Shamsh Kassim-Lakha, Executive Chairman of the Board Executive Committee, University of Central Asia (UCA), Kyrgyzstan\r\n\r\nPanelists:\r\n\r\n-	Matthew Hartley, Professor, Higher Education Division, University of Pennsylvania Graduate School of Education, USA\r\n\r\n-	Abdrakhman Naizabekov, Rector, Rudny Industrial Institute, Kazakhstan\r\n\r\n-	Ivan Klimenko, President, LLP "Stopharm", Kazakhstan\r\n<hr>\r\n4. Panel session: Role of TVET in Education\r\n\r\nModerator: Sabyrzhan Madeyev, Director, Department for Modernization of Vocational and Post-secondary Education of the Ministry of Education and Science of the Republic of Kazakhstan\r\n\r\nKeynote speaker: Geoff Hayward, Head of Education Faculty, University of Cambridge, UK\r\n\r\nPanelists:\r\n\r\n-	Kadyrbek Boribekov, Deputy Chairman, “Kassipkor” National Holding, Kazakhstan\r\n\r\n-	Rainer Goertz, Senior Expert TVET, GIZ Kazakhstan\r\n\r\n-	Marlen Mirzabekov, Chairman of the Management Board, LLP "Kazzinc Holdings", Kazakhstan\r\n\r\n-	Shokan Orazalin, Director, “Higher Technical School of Shchuchinsk” State Municipal, Kazakhstan\r\n<hr>\r\n5. Panel session: Student Transitions and Careers Guidance\r\n\r\nModerator: Kadisha Dairova, Vice-President for Student Affairs and International Cooperation, Nazarbayev University, Kazakshtan\r\n\r\nKeynote speaker: Dina Askarova, Student, School of Humanities and Social Sciences, Nazarbayev University, Kazakhstan\r\n\r\nPanelists:\r\n\r\n-	David Bridges, Professor, University of Cambridge, UK\r\n\r\n-	Sultan Imanzhan, Student, College of Transport and Communication, Kazakhstan\r\n\r\n-	Assel Mukhametzhanova, PhD student, Nazarbayev University Graduate School of Education, Kazakhstan\r\n<hr>\r\nClosing session:\r\n\r\nModerator: Shigeo Katsu, President, Nazarbayev University, Kazakhstan\r\n\r\nSpeakers:\r\n\r\n-	Isak Froumin, Academic Director, HSE Institute of Education, Russia\r\n\r\n-	Sue Bennett, Director of Student Careers and Skills, University of Warwick, UK', 'Speakers 2015', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '423-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-11-16 08:52:11', '2016-11-16 05:52:11', '', 423, 'http://ehelf.loc/2016/11/16/423-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(638, 1, '2016-11-16 08:55:10', '2016-11-16 05:55:10', 'Eurasian Higher Education Leaders Forum 2016\r\n\r\nHigher Education and Modernization of the Economy: Innovative and Entrepreneurial Universities\r\n<a href="http://triplehelix.stanford.edu/3helix_concept"><strong>The Triple Helix</strong></a> denotes that the potential for innovation and economic development in a Knowledge Society lies in a more prominent role for the university and in the hybridisation of elements from university, industry and government to generate new institutional and social formats for the production, transfer and application of knowledge. This vision particularly encompasses the creative renewal that arises within each of the three institutional spheres of university, industry and government, as well as at their intersections.\r\n\r\nThe panelists of the session will address the following issues:\r\n\r\n● The role of higher education in the modernization of the economy,\r\n\r\n● Entrepreneurial and innovative universities,\r\n\r\n● The future of universities,\r\n\r\n● Graduate employment and the needs of the economy.', 'Themes', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '279-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-11-16 08:55:10', '2016-11-16 05:55:10', '', 279, 'http://ehelf.loc/2016/11/16/279-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(639, 1, '2016-11-15 21:30:27', '2016-11-15 18:30:27', '<div style="float: left;width: 75%;display: block;">\r\n<img class="wp-image-74 aligncenter" src="http://ehelf.loc/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/313505.jpg" alt="313506" width="463" height="230" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Еуразия өңірінің білім беру саласындағы маңызды іс-шара жыл сайынғы Еуразиялық жоғары білім беру көшбасшыларының форумы 2016 жылдың 26 мамырында Назарбаев Университетінде өтеді.</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>\r\nФорумның негізгі мақсаты − мамандардың басын қосып, қазіргі таңдағы білім берудің ең өзекті мәселелері бойынша ашық пікірталас алаңын қалыптастыру. </strong>\r\n\r\n<center>[embed] https://www.youtube.com/watch?list=PL1EpAtH6eZQiO6HppmHyczS7tF19vt1wZ&v=Nm6delNpIpg  [/embed] </center>\r\n\r\n<strong>ФОРУМ ТАКЫРЫБЫ:</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>ЖОҒАРЫ БІЛІМ БЕРУ ЖӘНЕ ЭКОНОМИКА МОДЕРНИЗАЦИЯСЫ: ИННОВАЦИЯЛЫҚ ЖӘНЕ КӘСІПКЕРЛІК ЖОҒАРЫ ОҚУ ОРЫНДАРЫ</strong>\r\n\r\nБерілген сессия аясында пікірталасушылар келесі сұрақтарды қарастырады:\r\n\r\n	<li>Кәсіпкерлік жоғары оқу орындар</li>\r\n\r\n	<li>Жоғары білім берудің экономиканың дамуындағы атқарар рөлі </li>\r\n\r\n	<li>Болашақтың университеттері</li>\r\n\r\n	<li>Бітірушілердің жұмысқа орналастырылуы және экономиканың еңбек ресурстарындағы қажеттіліктері</li>\r\n\r\n\r\n<strong>ТІРКЕУ:</strong>\r\n\r\nҚатысушыларды тіркеу 2016 жылғы 15 мамырда  аяқталады.\r\n\r\n<strong>ФОРУМ ТІЛДЕРІ:</strong>\r\n\r\nКонференцияның жұмыс тілдері ағылшын, қазақ және орыс тілдері. Тіркелу орнында қалау бойынша ілеспе аударма қолжетімді болады. Аударма үш тілге жасалады: қазақ, орыс, ағылшын тілдері. Ілеспе аударманың құрылғысын алу тек жеке басты куәландыратын құжатты (паспорт, жеке куәлік) көрсетумен ғана жүзеге асырылатынына назарыңызды аударамыз.) көрсетумен ғана жүзеге асырылатынына назарыңызды аударамыз.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div id="sidebar" style="display: block;float: left;width: 25%;">\r\n	<div id="sidebar-core">\r\n\r\n	<aside class="widget widget_weblizar_twitter"><h3 class="widget-title">Tweets</h3>        <div style="display:block;width:100%;float:left;overflow:hidden">\r\n	    <a class="twitter-timeline" data-dnt="true" href="https://twitter.com/@NUedukz" \r\n		min-width="" \r\n		height="450" \r\n		data-theme="light" \r\n		data-lang=""\r\n		data-link-color=""></a>\r\n			<script>\r\n				!function(d,s,id) {\r\n					var js,fjs=d.getElementsByTagName(s)[0],p=/^http:/.test(d.location)?''http'':''https'';if(!d.getElementById(id)){js=d.createElement(s);js.id=id;js.src=p+"://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js";fjs.parentNode.insertBefore(js,fjs);}\r\n				} (document,"script","twitter-wjs");\r\n			</script>\r\n		</div>\r\n        </aside>\r\n		</div>\r\n<img class="wp-image-910 alignnone" src="http://ehelf.loc/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/AEF.gif" alt="aef" width="230" height="230" />\r\n		</div><!-- #sidebar --> ', 'Басты бет', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', '%d0%b1%d0%b0%d1%81%d1%82%d1%8b-%d0%b1%d0%b5%d1%82', '', '', '2016-11-24 17:47:53', '2016-11-24 14:47:53', '', 0, 'http://ehelf.loc/?page_id=639', 0, 'page', '', 0),
