(891, 1, '2016-11-20 08:00:06', '2016-11-20 05:00:06', '<div>\r\n<h1>Shigeo Katsu</h1>\r\n<img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-285" src="http://ehelf.loc/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/shigeo-300x296.jpg" alt="shigeo" width="300" height="296" />\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div><b>President, Nazarbayev University, Kazakhstan </b></div>\r\n<div><b> </b></div>\r\n<div> Since December 2010 Shigeo Katsu has served as President of the Nazarbayev University in Astana, Kazakhstan, a national university founded in June of the same year, designed to serve as the country''s flagship academic institution with aspirations to become a global level research university. Prior to this appointment, Mr. Katsu worked at the World Bank: he joined the World Bank as a Young Professional in 1979, and soon was assigned to the West Africa Region as an infrastructure economist, then as the Bank''s Resident Representative in Benin. He was seconded to the Export-Import Bank of Japan as Deputy Director, Country Economic Policy Analysis Department. Following successive assignments in the China Department, Cote d''Ivoire, and the Europe and Central Asia Region he became Vice President of the ECA Region, in which position he served for six years followed by a short stint as Special Advisor to the Managing Directors before retirement in December 2009. In addition to the above, Mr. Katsu consulted with the Asian Development Bank and the World Bank, advised governments, and collaborated with think tanks and not-for-profit organizations. He also served as the chair of the US Board of Restless Development, an international NGO that focuses on Youth development and mainstreaming of the Youth Agenda in national development strategies mainly in the African continent. He still is member of the board. Since May 2011, Mr. Katsu has served on the Advisory Panel to the Asean+3 Macro-economic Research Office.</div>', 'Shigeo Katsu', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '284-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-11-20 08:00:06', '2016-11-20 05:00:06', '', 284, 'http://ehelf.loc/2016/11/20/284-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(892, 1, '2016-11-20 08:01:18', '2016-11-20 05:01:18', '<strong>ЖОҒАРЫ БІЛІМ</strong><strong> БЕРУ</strong><strong> КӨШБАСШЫЛАРЫНЫҢ ЕУРАЗИЯЛЫҚ ФОРУМЫ-2016</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Жоғары білім беру және экономика</strong><strong>ны</strong> <strong>жаңғырту </strong><strong>: инновациялық және кәсі</strong><strong>би </strong><strong>жоғары оқу орындары</strong>\r\n\r\nИнновациялар мен қоғамның экономикалық дамуы үшін білімнің әлеуеті «<a href="http://triplehelix.stanford.edu/3helix_concept"><strong>ү</strong><strong>ш </strong><strong>спираль</strong></a><strong>» </strong>моделі шеңберінде жоғары оқу орныны, өнеркәсіп және үкімет арасындағы үшжақты  өзара іс-қимылда білімді  қалыптастыруда, беру мен қолдануда жаңа институционалдық және қоғамдық тәсілдерді әзірлеудің қажетті талабы ретіндегі университеттің рөлінің барынша мәнді болуымен айқындалады. Осы  тұжырымдама өзінде университеттің, өнеркәсіптің және үкіметтің креативті жаңаруын, оның ішінде олардың екіжақты және үшжақты өзара іс-қимыл нысандарының  жаңаруын қамтиды.\r\n\r\nОсы сессия аясында пікірталасқа қатысушылар келесі мәселелерді талқылайды:\r\n\r\n○ Кәсіптік  жоғары оқу орындары,\r\n\r\n○ жоғары білім берудің экономиканы дамытудағы атқаратын  рөлі,\r\n\r\n○ болашақтың университеттері,\r\n\r\n○ түлектердің  жұмысқа орналастырылуы және экономиканың еңбек ресурстарына  сұранысы.', 'Тақырыптар', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '751-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-11-20 08:01:18', '2016-11-20 05:01:18', '', 751, 'http://ehelf.loc/2016/11/20/751-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(893, 1, '2016-11-20 08:02:25', '2016-11-20 05:02:25', '<strong>“Library Connect - 2016:</strong>\r\n\r\nEmerging Global Trends in University Library Development”\r\n\r\nNazarbayev University Library, L.N. Gumilyov Eurasian National University Scientific Library and Academic Library Association of Kazakhstan in part with the Eurasian Higher Education Leaders Forum - 2016 hold:\r\n· Professional seminar “Library Connect - 2016: Emerging Global Trends in University Library Development”\r\n· V international conference “Modern Trends in University Library Development: state, issues, and perspectives-2016”\r\nfor senior specialists and managers of university libraries in Kazakhstan.\r\n\r\n<strong>Date:</strong> May 25-26, 2016\r\n<strong>Venue: </strong>Nazarbayev University and L.N. Gumilyov Eurasian National University\r\n\r\nThe measures will include lectures, workshops, and presentations by foreign and Kazakhstani academic librarians, as well as consultations and discussions regarding current issues in library and information services for educational and research activities at universities.\r\n\r\nParticipation in the seminar is free of charge.\r\n\r\nTravel, accommodation and meals costs are at the expenses of the participants or sending organizations.\r\n\r\n<strong>Registration</strong> of participants is opened: with presentation by April 30, 2016 (with a presentation) or May 17, 2016 (without a presentation):\r\n· on the Eurasian Higher Education Leaders Forum website - https://form.jotform.me/61032813893455\r\n· on the L.N. Gumilyov Eurasian National University Scientific library website - http://lib.enu.kz/kz/\r\n\r\n"Library Connect – 2016" seminar will be available online. Please follow this link to register for seminar''s Live Stream.\r\n\r\nThe program you can see <a href="http://ehelf.loc/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Forum_seminar_program_2016_eng.pdf"> <strong>here </strong></a>\r\n\r\nThe text of a paper for the conference proceedings should be sent to library@enu.kz no later than April 30, 2016.\r\n<strong>\r\nProceedings paper requirements:</strong>\r\nTitle, full author/coauthor name, institution, city, country.\r\nAbstract in 500 characters (including spaces).\r\nThe paper is accepted in electronic format only (Word for Windows; 14 font size, 1.5 line spacing).\r\nThe Organizing Committee reserves the right to include the papers into the program or the proceedings.\r\n<strong>\r\nContact information: </strong>\r\nAnar Dautova: adautova@nu.edu.kz (+7 7172-70-62-73+7 7172-70-62-73, 8-775-786-79-41)\r\nDarya Zvonareva: darya.zvonareva@nu.edu.kz (+7 7172-70-59-41+7 7172-70-59-41, 8-747-256-08-98)\r\n\r\n<strong>\r\nAbout participation and proceedings paper publication:</strong>\r\nGulshat Daribayeva: library@enu.kz (+ 7 (7172) 70-95-00+ 7 (7172) 70-95-00, 8 -777 331 36 628 -777 331 36 62)', 'Seminar for librarians', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '126-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-11-20 08:02:25', '2016-11-20 05:02:25', '', 126, 'http://ehelf.loc/2016/11/20/126-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
