(897, 1, '2016-11-20 08:04:42', '2016-11-20 05:04:42', '<strong>Sharing NU Experience</strong>\r\n\r\nMay 26, 2016\r\n\r\n<strong>Seminar: </strong>Learning and teaching at NU: Strategic Approaches\r\n\r\n<strong>Audience:</strong> faculty, administrative staff of universities, representatives from the Ministry of Education and Science of the Republic of Kazakhstan\r\n\r\nThis seminar is a platform for discussion of issues related to planning, teaching and assessment in higher education institutions of Kazakhstan taking into account the implementation of international experience.\r\n\r\n<strong>Topics for discussion:</strong>\r\n\r\n✓ Program development model at NU;\r\n✓ Learning and teaching at NU: strategic overview;\r\n✓ Professional development of faculty at NU.\r\n\r\n<strong>Important information:</strong>\r\n\r\nIn order to create a fruitful and useful discussion of the issues related to teaching experience, we are kindly asking those, who are interested in attending the seminar, to email us a list of questions to be raised at the session relevant to the proposed topics of discussion <strong>until May 15, 2016</strong> at dina.gungor@nu.edu.kz.\r\n\r\n<strong>Speakers:</strong>\r\n<a href="http://ehelf.loc/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Dina-Vyortkina-2.pdf"><strong>Dina Vyortkina</strong></a>, Head of Instructional Technology Department, Office of the Provost\r\nDunkan Priestley, Head of Academic Quality Enhancement Department, Office of the Provost\r\n\r\n<strong>Contact:</strong>\r\n+7 (7172) 70 90 52, Dina Vyortkina, dina.vyortkina@nu.edu.kz\r\n\r\n<strong>Program Seminar «Curriculum development, teaching and student assessment»</strong>\r\n\r\nDate: May 26, 2016\r\nVenue: Nazarbayev University, Block ___, Room ___\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<table>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>14:30 – 14:40</strong></td>\r\n<td>Registration</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong> 14:40 – 14:50 </strong></td>\r\n<td>Opening session</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>14:50 – 15:10</strong></td>\r\n<td>Program development model at NU</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>15:10 – 15:25</strong></td>\r\n<td>Learning and teaching at NU: strategic overview</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>15:25 – 15:40 </strong></td>\r\n<td>Professional development of faculty at NU</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>15:40 – 16:00</strong></td>\r\n<td>Q&amp;A</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong> 16:00 – 16:10</strong></td>\r\n<td>Concluding session</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>', 'Learning and teaching at NU', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '174-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-11-20 08:04:42', '2016-11-20 05:04:42', '', 174, 'http://ehelf.loc/2016/11/20/174-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(898, 1, '2016-11-20 08:07:18', '2016-11-20 05:07:18', '<strong>Sharing NU Experience</strong>\r\n\r\nMay 26, 2016\r\n\r\nSeminar: Implementing Corporate Governance in HEIs\r\n\r\n<strong>Audience:</strong> Members of governing boards of Kazakhstani HEIs, administrative staff of universities, representatives from the Ministry of Education and Science of the Republic of Kazakhstan, representatives from the Ministry of Health and Social Development\r\n\r\nThis seminar is a platform for discussion of issues related to enhancing HEI management in Kazakhstan, taking into account the implementation of the principles of corporate governance.\r\n\r\n<strong>Topics for discussion:</strong>\r\n\r\n✓ Corporate governance in higher education institutions;\r\n✓ Boards of Trustees;\r\n✓ Boards of Overseers.\r\n\r\n<strong>Important information:</strong>\r\n\r\nIn order to create a fruitful and useful discussion of the issues related to the implementation of corporate governance in HEIs, we are kindly asking those, who are interested in attending the seminar, to email us a list of questions to be raised at the seminar relevant to the proposed topics of discussion <strong>until May 15, 2016</strong> at dina.gungor@nu.edu.kz.\r\n<strong>Speakers:</strong>\r\nPeter Eckel, Director, Leadership Programs, Penn AHEAD, GSE, University of Pennsylvania (USA)\r\nDennis de Tray, Adviser to the President, Nazarbayev University\r\nYerden Kussain, General Counsel, Nazarbayev University\r\n\r\n<strong>Contact:</strong>\r\n+7 (7172) 70 66 30, Zakir Jumakulov, zakir.jumakulov@nu.edu.kz\r\n+7 (7172) 70 64 38, Dina Gungor, dina.gungor@nu.edu.kz\r\n\r\n<strong>Program\r\nSeminar: “Implementing Corporate Governance in HEIs”</strong>\r\n\r\nDate: May 26, 2016\r\nVenue: Nazarbayev University, Block ___, Room ____\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<table>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>11:15 – 11:30</strong></td>\r\n<td>Registration</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>11:30 – 11:35</strong></td>\r\n<td>Opening session</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>11:35 – 11:55</strong></td>\r\n<td>HEI Corporate Governance: principles, mechanisms, structure</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>11:55 – 12:10</strong></td>\r\n<td>NU Corporate Governance</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>12:10 – 12:25</strong></td>\r\n<td>Corporate Governance in Kazakhstani HEIs</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>12:25 – 12:40</strong></td>\r\n<td>Corporate Governance in a Kazakhstani University: experience gained from NUGSE PDP on HEI Corporate Governance and implemented at the university</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>12:40 – 13:10</strong></td>\r\n<td>Q&amp;A</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>13:10 – 13:15 </strong></td>\r\n<td>Concluding session</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>', 'NUGSE Governance', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '166-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-11-20 08:07:18', '2016-11-20 05:07:18', '', 166, 'http://ehelf.loc/2016/11/20/166-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(899, 1, '2016-11-20 08:07:39', '2016-11-20 05:07:39', 'Practicing Inclusion in Higher Education: Sharing NU GSE Experience\r\n\r\nMay 26, 2016\r\n\r\n14:30 – 16:00\r\n\r\nRoom: 1204\r\n\r\nNazarbayev University\r\n\r\nGraduate School of Education\r\n\r\n53 Kabanbay Batyr Ave., Astana\r\n\r\nThe purpose of this presentation is to share NU GSE experience on inclusive education. The participants of this event will be able to learn about NU GSE approach in organizing inclusive educational process and to discuss with NU GSE faculty and M.Sc. Inclusive Education degree students about practicing inclusion in higher education.\r\n\r\nThe language of the session: English\r\n\r\n14:30 – 14:35 Welcome\r\n\r\nRita Kaša, Assistant Professor\r\n\r\n14:35 – 14:50 What does it mean “inclusive education”? Principles of the best practice\r\n\r\n<a href="http://gse.nu.edu.kz/gse/MAIN/About/Faculty/FA0A84F7083232D7E040010AA9012A78"><strong>Daniel Torrano</strong></a>, Assistant Professor\r\n\r\n14:50 - 15:05 Organizing inclusive education process at NU GSE\r\n\r\n<a href="http://gse.nu.edu.kz/gse/MAIN/About/Faculty/FA0A6026931DB342E040010AA90128A4"><strong>Tsediso Makoelle</strong></a>, General Director for Research\r\n\r\n15:05 – 15:20 Experiencing inclusive education at NU GSE: A student perspective\r\n\r\nZiyat Abdykaimov, M.Sc. Inclusive Education student\r\n\r\n15:20 – 15:35 Practicing inclusive education at NU GSE: Faculty and staff perspectives\r\n\r\n<a href="http://gse.nu.edu.kz/gse/MAIN/About/Faculty/%D0%90%D0%BD%D0%BD%D0%B0%20%D0%A1%D0%B8%D0%BE%D0%BD%D0%B8%20%D0%9A%D0%BE%D1%85%D0%B5%D0%BD%D0%9C%D0%B8%D0%BB%D0%BB%D0%B5%D1%80" target="_blank"><strong>Anna CohenMiller</strong></a>, Assistant Professor\r\n\r\nKuralay Bozymbekova, Teaching Assistant\r\n\r\nMargaret Spires, NU GSE Subject Librarian\r\n\r\n15:35 – 15:55 Q&amp;A and discussion\r\n\r\n15:55 – 16:00 Concluding remarks', 'NUGSE Inclusive Education', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '177-revision-v1', '', '', '20